===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[rikaz]]'' (''*rīk-, *rīkja-''), from Celtic ''*rīgiom'' ‘kingdom’, from ''*rīgs'' ‘king’ (compare Irish ''[[rí]]''), from Indo-European ''*rēgs'' ‘king’.
Cognates include Old Saxon ''rīki'' (Dutch ''[[rijk]]''), Old High German ''[[rīhhi]]'' (German ''[[Reich]]'', ''[[reich]]''), Old Norse ''[[ríki]]'' ''n'', ''[[ríkr]]'' ''adj'' (Swedish ''[[rike]]'' ''n'', ''[[rik]]'' ''adj''), Gothic [[𐍂𐌴𐌹𐌺𐌹]] ''n'', [[𐍂𐌴𐌹𐌺𐌴𐌹𐍃]] ''adj''.  The IE root is also the source of Latin ''[[rex]]''.

